modules.description: Provides functions to create, compare, and serialize instances of type t, which represent proof objects in a verification system. Includes operations to check the validity of proofs and extract embedded values. Used to enforce type-level constraints in dependently typed programs.

Generates unique identifiers with type-safe tagging, allowing conversion between witness types and opaque representations. Operates on polymorphic witness types and opaque token structures. Enables safe comparison and equality checks for distinct type-erased values.

Compares two strings lexicographically using a total ordering function, returning an integer indicating their relative order. Converts strings to their canonical string representation. Used to sort string-based keys in data structures or generate consistent string outputs for logging and display.

Compares integer values using a total ordering, returning -1, 0, or 1 based on the relationship between two inputs. Converts integer values to their string representations for display or logging. Used to sort lists of integers or generate human-readable output from numeric data.

Provides functions to create, compare, and serialize instances of type t, including a verification method that checks structural equality. Operates on opaque data structures representing logical proofs or constraints. Used to validate input consistency in theorem-proving workflows and ensure data integrity in formal verification systems.

Compares values of type t using a total ordering, returning an integer result based on their relative positions. Converts values of type t to their string representations for debugging or logging purposes. Used to enforce consistent ordering in sorted data structures and to generate human-readable output for internal state inspection.

Compares values of type t using a total ordering, returning an integer result based on their relative positions. Converts values of type t to their string representations. Used to standardize comparisons and human-readable outputs for custom data types.

Sorts and inspects values of type t using total ordering and string conversion. Provides comparison operations to determine relative positions and debugging outputs for internal states. Enables consistent sorting and readable representation of custom data types. For example, it can order a list of documents by their TF-IDF scores or display their internal structure for analysis.

Provides lexicographic and numeric comparison capabilities with canonical conversions. Supports sorting and consistent output generation for strings and integers. Returns ordered results for comparisons and converts values to string representations. Enables structured data sorting and reliable logging of textual and numeric information.

Manages opaque logical proof and constraint structures with creation, comparison, and serialization capabilities. Includes a structural equality check to validate consistency in theorem-proving and formal verification. Operations support input validation and data integrity verification. Examples include checking proof validity and converting constraint representations for storage or transmission.

Provides functions to build and query monomorphic search indexes using unique identifiers. Operates on strings and associative arrays to enable efficient text-based lookups. Used to implement full-text search in applications requiring fast, in-memory indexing of structured data.

Compares elements of type t using a total ordering, returning an integer indicating their relative position. Converts elements of type t to human-readable string representations. Used to sort and display search results based on custom key comparisons.
